    {
      "id": "0b00fdea296a0c8cd92e61e1e35c45b275b1b856",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2024-03-17 03:02:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nOther than confusing failures in dkms this should be okay.\nIs there a way to communicate 'modules_prepare' to configure?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "347e6687b98040473e4882e7e7076197e6fc706a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2024-03-20 01:06:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nCommunicating 'modules_prepare' to configure? I'm not sure - I can take a look when I get a chance.\n\nAbout dkms, what do the other optional LNDs do? Perhaps the configure script could fail if an explicit flag is passed (--with-o2ib or whatever) and succeed otherwise?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0634601ae680514dfa9d2d30cdf441796637ead8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2024-03-20 02:34:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> Communicating 'modules_prepare' to configure? I'm not sure - I can take a look when I get a chance.\n> \n> About dkms, what do the other optional LNDs do? Perhaps the configure script could fail if an explicit flag is passed (--with-o2ib or whatever) and succeed otherwise?\n\nYes I added a patch to enable /etc/sysconfig/lustre to pass flags to dkms configure.\nThe only problem is there is a 'guess' phase the tries to determine what LNDs should build and an install phase that *expects* to guess to have been correct.\n\nThe optional LNDs are for different interconnect hardware (mofed, OPA, slingshot, ...)\n\nWe could go the other direction and have DKMS to pass a flag to configure as the inverse of adding a flag for modules_prepare, that should be pretty straight forward.\n\nAnyway not a reason to block this patch, imo.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
